The Trade Minister's popularity is tumbling ahead of a major vote tonight that will see another MP eliminated from the contest. A YouGov poll last week suggested that Ms Mordaunt would comfortably win the run-off against any of the other candidates. But on Monday, polling by Smarket found Ms Mordaunt in third position to be the next Tory leader; down to 18.87 percent, behind Liz Truss on 28.17 percent and Rishi Sunak on 45.45 percent. This pessimism is echoed in a survey by ConservativeHome that suggested both Mr Sunak and Ms Truss had risen above Mordaunt in the estimation of Tory members. A team Mordaunt source told Express.co.uk: "It looks like it's falling apart." FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...